vel the quest just by doing it.<br><br>3.  On a scale of 1 to 10 please rate how screewed you are.  I think I'm an 8.<br><br>4.  Any tips on how to unscrew myself? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/14/01 1:40:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=900.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: (Beastlord Quests)  Is there anyway to de-lvl from 6 to </span><hr size=1> Just die until you hit 5 again.  Scorpion legs didn't trivial to me until level 9, though, so you might just want to look around for tougher scorpions and of course those pesky young rockhoppers.  Also keep an eye out for any merchants that newbies sell to who don't know about the quests...sometimes you can get quest items for just a few copper.<br><br>If you think that's bad though, how about finding your low level rogue quest at about the time you hit level 11, and everyone eats Rockhopper eggs.  Hmph.<br><br>Reoqim<br>Lords of Discipline<br>12th Claw <p><center><i>"Sings we a dance of wolfs,<br>Who smells fear and slays the coward.<br>Sings we a dance of mans,<br>Who smells gold and slays his brother."</i><p>--Pagan Saying</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 11:53:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=900.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: (Beastlord Quests)  Is there anyway to de-lvl from 6 to </span><hr size=1> Say, Madrain!  What exactly do you get when you do the Vah Shir rogue quest(s)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhaqimofsharvahl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haqim of SharVahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 1:29:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=900.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: (Beastlord Quests)  Is there anyway to de-lvl from 6 to </span><hr size=1> 6 is not too late, although it will be annoying.  I actually leveled to 7 in the Newbie pit just seeking out the Rare Blue Scorpion and Young Rockhopper for my quest parts.<br><br>I actually have a few Scorpion Legs left I might be willing to help out a fellow Khati Sha with, but you are on your own for Young Rockhopper Claws.<br><br>As an aside, train up your Tailoring Skill first!  I wasted the Claws and Forged Fasteners Twice on combine failures! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/01 2:16:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=900.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: (Beastlord Quests)  Is there anyway to de-lvl from 6 to </span><hr size=1> From someone who's watched a friend go thru it twice.<br><br>A newbie Vah Shir Beastlord walk thru.<br><br>Level 1 -- do the registration quest.  Kill needlehoppers to level up.<br><br>Level 2 thru 6<br>-- Kill scorpions and youngrockhoppers.  Don't even think of attacking anything else unless it's light blue or green.  You'll want to start collecting tons of scorpion legs and young rockhopper claws in the bank.<br>-- Once you have the legs and claws, go out to the Thicket and kill worms for silk, or needlehoppers for HQ hide<br>-- make your handwraps<br>-- make your claws<br>-- reinforce the claws<br><br>Level 3 thru 8<br>-- if you're lucky, you could make your claws with a lucky combine.  Don't proceed to this stage until you get your claws.  Scorpions and Young rockhoppers are mostly lt-blue and green by the time you reach level 7.<br>-- go to the Thicket and do the +HP armor quests (good for beyond level <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>-- lesser shades provide Xacra armor that can be combined to produce shaded armor -- usually better than tattered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=900.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=900.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=900.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=900.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregiste